Convent Avenue, west side, from 150th to 149th Street. Hamilton Grange Reformed Church is at the left in the background. At the right is 450-460 West 150th Street, at adjoining, and west of the S.W. corner of Convent Avenue. The six houses comprising the numbers from 450-460 are all 2½-story frame houses.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 376

Convent Avenue, east side, north across West 149th Street, showing at the right, the Cosmopolitan Tennis Club. This is hidden behind the sign boards on the Avenue. View 2 is limited to the entrance between the billboards.

May 19, 1940
No's. 1-2

P. L. Sperr
